<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,823,1559]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,354,898,924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Description.</emphasis>
Colouration (
<figureCitation box="[525,601,898,924]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,269,2011,2035]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,747,1999]" captionTargetId="figure-266@2.[151,1436,742,2003]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Habitus. 1—Roscius diversus sp. nov., ♂, holotype; 2—Roscius niger sp. nov., ♀, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302998/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Head both dorsally and ventrally, as well as all ventrites and outer female genitalia red. Pronotum (except lateral and posterior margin), scutellum, clavus, corium, membrane, pleura I–III, basisterna I–III, legs, antennae and labium black. Lateral (narrowly) and posterior margin (more widely) of pronotum, prosternal collar, pronotal epipleuron, posterior pleural flanges I–III and epicoxal lobes I–III yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,823,1559]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Structure. Head horizontally positioned, eye temple very small, antennifer large, protruding sideways, antennae long, jugum not gibbose, narrowed towards its apex, tightly adjoining clypeus. Labium surpassing half of the ventrite IV. Pronotum anteriorly conspicuously narrowed, sides of pronotal lobes remarkably divergent towards its base, pronotal lobe remarkably convex towards base.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,823,1559]" box="[197,562,1234,1260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
Outer female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[475,547,1234,1260]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="3.[151,269,570,594]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,197,549]" captionTargetId="figure-323@3.[151,1436,197,549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. 3–4—Roscius diversus sp. nov. 3–pygophore, dorsal view; 4—outer female genitalia. 5—Roscius niger sp. nov., outer female genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303000/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,823,1559]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
Measurements (mm). Female (
<typeStatus box="[567,679,1272,1298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">holotype</typeStatus>
). Body length 16.47; head: length 2.21, width (including eyes) 2.19, interocular width 1.08; lengths of antennomeres: 1—2.97, 2—3.29, 3—2.21, 4—2.65; pronotum: length 2.97, width 4.70; scutellum: length 2.27, width 2.70; corium: length 9.18, width 2.97.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
