<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,823,1559]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,1458,1484]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is composed from the Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stehlík &amp; Jindra" authorityYear="2010" box="[1042,1104,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrrhocoridae" genus="Roscius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis box="[1042,1104,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, - 
<emphasis box="[1129,1144,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[1170,1206,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">um</emphasis>
, meaning black, in reference to its unique colouration of hemelytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
